@node "Intro" "Introduction"
    This is the Amiga port of mSQL V2.0.6 It was compiled with GeekGadget2.
    This distribution match the original distribution with, in addition,
    - Amiga binaries.
    - AmigaGuide User Manual.
    - Installer script.

    With that, you should be able to quickly setup & run a mSQL server.
        Enjoy!

Christophe Sollet. (cfc@iname.com) http://altern.org/amsql
@endnode

@node "Install" "Install"

    Use the installer script!

    Go to the msql: directory and check that the msql.conf file match your
        need.
        Please read the original documentation for more information.
@endnode

@node "Contact" "Amiga mSQL Contact"

    Mike Erasmus
    horror@smartnet.co.za

    Christophe Sollet
    cfc@iname.com

@endnode

@node "msqll" "Msql.library"

    If you are thinking about accessing a msql server in your own
developement,
    check the msql.library.
    This shared library include all the client code side of msql.

    Information & Download: - http://altern.org/cfc/msql
        or ~aminet/biz/dbase/MsqlLib.lha

@endnode

